{
  "guid": "xaoc",
  "name": "Chaos",
  "description": "This algorithm generates chaotic CVs according to a variety of so-called 'attractors', including the well-known Lorenz equations. Each generates three CVs, named X, Y, and Z, which are available on separate outputs. You can modify the parameters of the Lorenz equation – 'Rho mod' affects 'r' (aka 'ρ'), and 'Beta mod' affects 'b' (aka 'β'). With the values at 0V, the parameters are the classic values as studied by Lorenz (64 and 8/3 respectively).",
  "categories": [
    "chaos",
    "cv",
    "attractor",
    "lorenz"
  ],
  "short_description": "CVs from the Lorenz equations",
  "gui_description": "The display shows a graphical representation of the outputs, projected onto the X/Y, X/Z, and Y/Z planes.",
